+import { readFileSync } from 'fs';
+import { CharacterSettings } from '@elizaos/core';
+
+async function updateObsidianKnowledge() {
+    try {
+        const characterSettingsPath = process.argv[2];
+        if (!characterSettingsPath) {
+            throw new Error('Character settings path not provided');
+        }
+
+        const characterSettings: CharacterSettings = JSON.parse(readFileSync(characterSettingsPath, 'utf-8'
));
+
+        // Send the create knowledge base command
+        const response = await fetch(`http://localhost:3000/${characterSettings.name}/message`, {
+            method: 'POST',
+            headers: {
+                'Content-Type': 'application/json',
+            },
+            body: JSON.stringify({
+                userId: "system",
+                userName: "system",
+                text: "Create knowledge base",
+                action: "CREATE_KNOWLEDGE",
+                options: {
+                    chunkSize: 50000,  // Process in 50k token chunks
+                    chunkOverlap: 100  // 100 token overlap between chunks
+                }
+            })
+        });
+
+        if (!response.ok) {
+            throw new Error(`Failed to update knowledge base: ${response.statusText}`);
+        }
+
+        const result = await response.json();
+        console.log('Knowledge base update completed:', result);
+
+    } catch (error) {
+        console.error('Error updating Obsidian knowledge base:', error);
+        process.exit(1);
+    }
+}
+
+updateObsidianKnowledge();

+CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION search_memories(
+    query_table_name TEXT,
+    query_roomId UUID,
+    query_embedding vector,
+    query_match_threshold FLOAT DEFAULT 0.8,
+    query_match_count INT DEFAULT 10,
+    query_unique BOOLEAN DEFAULT true
+)
+RETURNS TABLE (
+    id UUID,
+    type TEXT,
+    "createdAt" TIMESTAMPTZ,
+    content JSONB,
+    embedding vector,
+    "userId" UUID,
+    "agentId" UUID,

+DECLARE
+    query TEXT;
+BEGIN
+    query := format('
+        SELECT *, 1 - (embedding <=> $1) as similarity
+        FROM %I
+        WHERE "roomId" = $2
+        AND ($6 = false OR "unique" = true)
+        AND 1 - (embedding <=> $1) > $3
+        ORDER BY similarity DESC
+        LIMIT $4
+    ', query_table_name);
+
+    RETURN QUERY EXECUTE query
+    USING query_embedding, query_roomId, query_match_threshold, query_match_cou
nt, query_match_threshold, q
uery_unique;
                            +END;
+$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql;

+    query_table_name TEXT,
+    query_threshold FLOAT,
+    query_input TEXT,
+    query_field_name TEXT,
+    query_field_sub_name TEXT,
+    query_match_count INT DEFAULT 10
+)
+RETURNS TABLE (

+DECLARE
+    query TEXT;

+    query := format('

+        FROM %I
+        WHERE content->>%L IS NOT NULL
+        AND levenshtein(%L, content->>%L) < %L
+        ORDER BY levenshtein_score ASC
+        LIMIT %L
+    ', query_input, query_field_sub_name, query_table_name, query_field_name, q
uery_input, query_field_sub_
name, query_threshold, query_match_count);
                            +
+    RETURN QUERY EXECUTE query;
+END;
